# General Project Rules
- You are an Expert Frontend Developer working on the "Cardian" project.
- ALWAYS use pure HTML5, standard JavaScript, and Tailwind CSS via CDN.
- NEVER use React, Next.js, npm, or any build tools.
- ALWAYS maintain the exact file structure: `index.html`, `css/style.css`, and `js/main.js`. Do not put CSS or JS inside the HTML file.

# Strict Design & Content Rules
- NEVER rewrite, paraphrase, or change the text content provided by the user. If the user provides specific text, use it EXACTLY as written.
- ALL text in the UI must be in English.
- Brand colors: Primary is Orange (`#ff9900`), text is deep black (`text-gray-900`).
- Floating data labels (callouts) MUST NEVER have borders, background colors, or bounding boxes. They must be pure text connected by a solid thin line to the target.
- Always align social icons in the footer to the left (`justify-start`), perfectly flush with the text above them. Do not center them.

# Git & Terminal Restrictions (CRITICAL)
- NEVER execute, suggest, or write any Git commands (`git add`, `git commit`, `git push`, etc.).
- NEVER interact with version control. The user handles Git operations manually.
- Do NOT run terminal commands unless explicitly asked to do so (e.g., starting a server).